### DMS-1145 — Link Injection on Document References (Read Path)
#
# Manual walkthrough of the link-injection contract for the relational read path:
#   - GET-by-id and query responses decorate every document-reference object with
#     `link.rel` (target resource name) and `link.href` (relative URI of the target).
#   - Descriptors continue to be serialized as URI strings — they do NOT get a `link`
#     envelope. Only document references (the `*Reference` objects that resolve to
#     other resources) participate in link injection.
#   - Link emission is keyset-deduplicated: a reference that appears N times in a
#     page emits N decorated links from a single auxiliary lookup.
#
# Two demo resource chains:
#
#   (A) CalendarDate chain — straightforward: root-level references + descriptor URIs.
#       LEA → School → SchoolYearType → Calendar → CalendarDate
#
#   (B) BellSchedule chain — the "interesting" case: a root-level reference
#       (schoolReference) PLUS multiple nested-collection-scoped references
#       (classPeriods[*].classPeriodReference). This is the same shape pinned by
#       E2E ProfileReferenceFiltering.feature scenario 05 and exercises page-level
#       dedup when both ClassPeriods share the same target School.
#       LEA → School → ClassPeriod ×2 → BellSchedule
#
# Expected on GET CalendarDate:
#   calendarReference: { calendarCode, schoolId, schoolYear, link: { rel: "Calendar", href: "/ed-fi/calendars/<uuid>" } }
#   calendarEvents[*].calendarEventDescriptor: "uri://ed-fi.org/CalendarEventDescriptor#Holiday"  (string, NO link)
#
# Expected on GET Calendar:
#   schoolReference:         { schoolId, link: { rel: "School", href: "/ed-fi/schools/<uuid>" } }
#   schoolYearTypeReference: { schoolYear, link: { rel: "SchoolYearType", href: "/ed-fi/schoolYearTypes/<uuid>" } }
#   calendarTypeDescriptor:  "uri://ed-fi.org/CalendarTypeDescriptor#Student Specific"  (string, NO link)
#
# Expected on GET BellSchedule:
#   schoolReference:                              { schoolId, link: { rel: "School",      href: "/ed-fi/schools/<uuid>" } }
#   classPeriods[0].classPeriodReference:         { schoolId, classPeriodName, link: { rel: "ClassPeriod", href: "/ed-fi/classPeriods/<uuid>" } }
#   classPeriods[1].classPeriodReference:         { schoolId, classPeriodName, link: { rel: "ClassPeriod", href: "/ed-fi/classPeriods/<uuid>" } }
#
# Prereqs:
#   /e2e start --relational          # link injection is a relational-backend feature
#   /e2e status                      # confirm ed-fi-api is healthy
#
# Execute top-to-bottom with the VS Code REST Client extension.

@dmsPort=8080
@configPort=8081
@dataApi=http://localhost:{{dmsPort}}/data

@sysAdminId=DmsConfigurationService
@sysAdminSecret=ValidClientSecret1234567890!Abcd

# Relational DB + password match eng/docker-compose/.env.e2e.relational.
@relationalDbName=edfi_datamanagementservice_relational
@postgresPassword=abcdefgh1!

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Bootstrap — Configuration Service token, vendor, DMS instance, application, DMS token
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1.1 Configuration-Service token
# @name configTokenRequest
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

client_id={{sysAdminId}}
&client_secret={{sysAdminSecret}}
&grant_type=client_credentials
&scope=edfi_admin_api/full_access

###
@configToken={{configTokenRequest.response.body.access_token}}

### 1.2 Create a vendor scoped to the ed-fi namespace
# @name createVendor
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/v3/vendors
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}

{
    "company": "DMS-1145 Link Injection Demo Vendor {{$randomInt 0 9999999}}",
    "contactName": "Relational Backend",
    "contactEmailAddress": "demo@example.com",
    "namespacePrefixes": "uri://ed-fi.org"
}

###
@vendorLocation={{createVendor.response.headers.location}}

### Retrieve the vendor to read the Id (POST returns no body per DMS-1081; id is the last segment of the Location header)
# @name getVendor
GET {{vendorLocation}}
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}

###
@vendorId={{getVendor.response.body.id}}

### 1.3 Create a DMS instance pointing at the RELATIONAL database
# @name createDataStore
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/v3/dataStores
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}

{
    "dataStoreType": "Test",
    "name": "DMS-1145 Link Injection Instance",
    "connectionString": "host=dms-postgresql;port=5432;username=postgres;password={{postgresPassword}};database={{relationalDbName}};"
}

###
@dataStoreId={{createDataStore.response.body.id}}

### 1.4 Create an application with NoFurtherAuthorizationRequired
# (matches the E2E relational-backend lane; avoids namespace-authz noise for the demo)
# @name createApplication
POST http://localhost:{{configPort}}/v3/applications
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: bearer {{configToken}}

{
    "vendorId": {{vendorId}},
    "applicationName": "DMS-1145 Link Injection Demo",
    "claimSetName": "E2E-NoFurtherAuthRequiredClaimSet",
    "educationOrganizationIds": [ 255, 255901 ],
    "dataStoreIds": [ {{dataStoreId}} ]
}

###
@clientId={{createApplication.response.body.key}}
@clientSecret={{createApplication.response.body.secret}}

### 1.5 Reload claim sets so the NoFurtherAuthRequired set is visible to DMS
POST http://localhost:{{dmsPort}}/management/reload-claimsets

### 1.6 Exchange the client credentials for a DMS bearer token
# Use HTTP Basic auth (not form-body) — the generated client_secret can contain '&'
# which would be interpreted as a form-encoded field separator.
# @name dmsTokenRequest
POST http://localhost:{{dmsPort}}/oauth/token
Authorization: basic {{clientId}}:{{clientSecret}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials

###
@dmsToken={{dmsTokenRequest.response.body.access_token}}

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. Seed descriptors (no `link` injection — these stay as URI strings)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 2.1 GradeLevelDescriptor — First grade
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/gradeLevelDescriptors
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "namespace": "uri://ed-fi.org/GradeLevelDescriptor",
    "codeValue": "First grade",
    "shortDescription": "First grade"
}

### 2.2 EducationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor — School
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/educationOrganizationCategoryDescriptors
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "namespace": "uri://ed-fi.org/EducationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor",
    "codeValue": "School",
    "shortDescription": "School"
}

### 2.3 LocalEducationAgencyCategoryDescriptor — Independent
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/localEducationAgencyCategoryDescriptors
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "namespace": "uri://ed-fi.org/LocalEducationAgencyCategoryDescriptor",
    "codeValue": "Independent",
    "shortDescription": "Independent"
}

### 2.4 CalendarTypeDescriptor — Student Specific
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/calendarTypeDescriptors
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "namespace": "uri://ed-fi.org/CalendarTypeDescriptor",
    "codeValue": "Student Specific",
    "shortDescription": "Student Specific"
}

### 2.5 CalendarEventDescriptor — Holiday
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/calendarEventDescriptors
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "namespace": "uri://ed-fi.org/CalendarEventDescriptor",
    "codeValue": "Holiday",
    "shortDescription": "Holiday"
}

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. Seed the document chain — LEA → School → SchoolYearType → Calendar → CalendarDate
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3.1 LocalEducationAgency 255 (parent of School)
# @name createLea
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/localEducationAgencies
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "localEducationAgencyId": 255,
    "nameOfInstitution": "Grand Bend ISD",
    "localEducationAgencyCategoryDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/LocalEducationAgencyCategoryDescriptor#Independent",
    "categories": [
        { "educationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/EducationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor#School" }
    ]
}

###
@leaLocation={{createLea.response.headers.location}}

### 3.2 School 255901 (referenced by Calendar.schoolReference)
# @name createSchool
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/schools
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "schoolId": 255901,
    "nameOfInstitution": "Grand Bend Elementary School",
    "localEducationAgencyReference": { "localEducationAgencyId": 255 },
    "educationOrganizationCategories": [
        { "educationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/EducationOrganizationCategoryDescriptor#School" }
    ],
    "gradeLevels": [
        { "gradeLevelDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/GradeLevelDescriptor#First grade" }
    ]
}

###
@schoolLocation={{createSchool.response.headers.location}}

### 3.3 SchoolYearType 2025 (referenced by Calendar.schoolYearTypeReference)
# @name createSchoolYearType
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/schoolYearTypes
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "schoolYear": 2025,
    "currentSchoolYear": true,
    "schoolYearDescription": "2024-2025"
}

###
@schoolYearTypeLocation={{createSchoolYearType.response.headers.location}}

### 3.4 Calendar (referenced by CalendarDate.calendarReference)
# Has TWO document references (schoolReference, schoolYearTypeReference) +
# one descriptor (calendarTypeDescriptor) — exercises both code paths on GET.
# @name createCalendar
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/calendars
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "calendarCode": "2024-2025-GBE",
    "schoolReference": { "schoolId": 255901 },
    "schoolYearTypeReference": { "schoolYear": 2025 },
    "calendarTypeDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/CalendarTypeDescriptor#Student Specific"
}

###
@calendarLocation={{createCalendar.response.headers.location}}

### 3.5 CalendarDate (root-level calendarReference + descriptor-only collection)
# @name createCalendarDate
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/calendarDates
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "calendarReference": {
        "calendarCode": "2024-2025-GBE",
        "schoolId": 255901,
        "schoolYear": 2025
    },
    "date": "2024-12-25",
    "calendarEvents": [
        { "calendarEventDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/CalendarEventDescriptor#Holiday" }
    ]
}

###
@calendarDateLocation={{createCalendarDate.response.headers.location}}

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. The actual link-injection demonstrations
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 4.1 GET Calendar — verify links on schoolReference + schoolYearTypeReference,
###     and verify calendarTypeDescriptor stays as a plain URI string
#
# Expected response shape (relevant fields only):
#   {
#     "id": "<uuid>",
#     "calendarCode": "2024-2025-GBE",
#     "schoolReference": {
#       "schoolId": 255901,
#       "link": { "rel": "School",         "href": "/ed-fi/schools/<school-uuid>" }
#     },
#     "schoolYearTypeReference": {
#       "schoolYear": 2025,
#       "link": { "rel": "SchoolYearType", "href": "/ed-fi/schoolYearTypes/<syt-uuid>" }
#     },
#     "calendarTypeDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/CalendarTypeDescriptor#Student Specific",
#     "_etag": "...",
#     "_lastModifiedDate": "..."
#   }
GET {{calendarLocation}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 4.2 GET CalendarDate — verify link on calendarReference,
###     and verify calendarEvents[*].calendarEventDescriptor stays as a plain URI string
#
# Expected response shape:
#   {
#     "id": "<uuid>",
#     "calendarReference": {
#       "calendarCode": "2024-2025-GBE",
#       "schoolId": 255901,
#       "schoolYear": 2025,
#       "link": { "rel": "Calendar", "href": "/ed-fi/calendars/<calendar-uuid>" }
#     },
#     "date": "2024-12-25",
#     "calendarEvents": [
#       { "calendarEventDescriptor": "uri://ed-fi.org/CalendarEventDescriptor#Holiday" }
#     ],
#     "_etag": "...",
#     "_lastModifiedDate": "..."
#   }
GET {{calendarDateLocation}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 4.3 Query Calendars — same link contract over a page
# Expected: each item in the result array carries the same `schoolReference.link`
# and `schoolYearTypeReference.link` decorations as the single-document GET above.
# Multiple calendars pointing at the same School/SchoolYearType still produce
# correctly populated link objects per row (page-level lookup dedup).
GET {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/calendars
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 4.4 Query CalendarDates — same link contract over a page
GET {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/calendarDates
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Accept: application/json

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. BellSchedule — root-level reference + multiple nested-collection references
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 5.1 ClassPeriod 1 — "First Period" on School 255901
# @name createClassPeriod1
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/classPeriods
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "classPeriodName": "First Period",
    "schoolReference": { "schoolId": 255901 }
}

###
@classPeriod1Location={{createClassPeriod1.response.headers.location}}

### 5.2 ClassPeriod 2 — "Second Period" on the same School
# @name createClassPeriod2
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/classPeriods
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "classPeriodName": "Second Period",
    "schoolReference": { "schoolId": 255901 }
}

###
@classPeriod2Location={{createClassPeriod2.response.headers.location}}

### 5.3 BellSchedule — root-level schoolReference + nested classPeriods with TWO references
# @name createBellSchedule
POST {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/bellSchedules
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "bellScheduleName": "Link Injection Demo Schedule",
    "schoolReference": { "schoolId": 255901 },
    "classPeriods": [
        { "classPeriodReference": { "schoolId": 255901, "classPeriodName": "First Period" } },
        { "classPeriodReference": { "schoolId": 255901, "classPeriodName": "Second Period" } }
    ]
}

###
@bellScheduleLocation={{createBellSchedule.response.headers.location}}

### 5.4 GET BellSchedule — the headline demonstration
#
# Three injected links to verify:
#   - schoolReference.link.rel  == "School"
#   - schoolReference.link.href ends with "/ed-fi/schools/<school-uuid>"
#   - classPeriods[0].classPeriodReference.link.rel  == "ClassPeriod"
#   - classPeriods[0].classPeriodReference.link.href ends with "/ed-fi/classPeriods/<cp1-uuid>"
#   - classPeriods[1].classPeriodReference.link.rel  == "ClassPeriod"
#   - classPeriods[1].classPeriodReference.link.href ends with "/ed-fi/classPeriods/<cp2-uuid>"
#
# Two ClassPeriods → two DISTINCT hrefs (different document UUIDs).
# Both ClassPeriods share the same target School slug, demonstrating that the
# page-level auxiliary lookup dedup still produces correct per-row decorations.
GET {{bellScheduleLocation}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 5.5 Query BellSchedules — page-level link contract
# Same contract applied to every item in the result array.
GET {{dataApi}}/ed-fi/bellSchedules
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
Accept: application/json

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. Cleanup (optional)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Delete BellSchedule
DELETE {{bellScheduleLocation}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

### Delete ClassPeriod 2
DELETE {{classPeriod2Location}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

### Delete ClassPeriod 1
DELETE {{classPeriod1Location}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

### Delete CalendarDate (uses the Location header captured above)
DELETE {{calendarDateLocation}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

### Delete Calendar
DELETE {{calendarLocation}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

### Delete SchoolYearType
DELETE {{schoolYearTypeLocation}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

### Delete School
DELETE {{schoolLocation}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}

### Delete LEA
DELETE {{leaLocation}}
Authorization: bearer {{dmsToken}}
